# 🐧 Linux Cheat Sheet

A quick reference guide for commonly used Linux commands.

---

# 📁 File & Directory Management

```bash
pwd                     # Show current directory
ls                      # List files
ls -la                  # List all files with details
cd directory_name       # Change directory
cd ..                   # Move one directory back
mkdir test              # Create directory
rmdir test              # Remove empty directory
rm -r test              # Remove directory and contents
touch file.txt          # Create file
cp file1 file2          # Copy file
mv file1 file2          # Move/Rename file
rm file.txt             # Delete file
```

---

# 📄 Viewing File Contents

```bash
cat file.txt            # Display file contents
less file.txt           # View file page by page
head file.txt           # First 10 lines
tail file.txt           # Last 10 lines
tail -f log.txt         # Monitor file updates
```

---

# 🔍 Searching Files & Text

```bash
find / -name file.txt               # Find file
find . -type f                      # Find files
grep "word" file.txt                # Search word in file
grep -r "word" .                    # Recursive search
which python                        # Locate executable
whereis python                      # Find binary/source/manual
locate filename                     # Locate file quickly
```

---

# 🔑 Permissions & Ownership

```bash
ls -l                   # View permissions
chmod 755 script.sh     # Change permissions
chmod +x script.sh      # Make executable
chown user:user file    # Change ownership
```

### Permission Values

| Value | Permission |
|---------|-----------|
| 7 | rwx |
| 6 | rw- |
| 5 | r-x |
| 4 | r-- |

---

# 👤 User Management

```bash
whoami                  # Current user
id                      # User info
sudo command            # Run as root
passwd                  # Change password
adduser username        # Add user
deluser username        # Delete user
usermod                 # Modify user
groups                  # Show user groups
```

---

# ⚙️ Process Management

```bash
ps                      # Running processes
ps aux                  # Detailed process list
top                     # Live process monitor
htop                    # Better process monitor
kill PID                # Kill process
kill -9 PID             # Force kill process
pkill process_name      # Kill by name
jobs                    # Background jobs
bg                      # Run job in background
fg                      # Bring job to foreground
```

---

# 🌐 Networking Commands

```bash
ip a                    # Show IP addresses
ifconfig                # Network info (older systems)
ping google.com         # Connectivity test
netstat -tulnp          # Open ports
ss -tulnp               # Modern netstat
traceroute google.com   # Trace route
nslookup google.com     # DNS lookup
dig google.com          # Detailed DNS lookup
arp -a                  # ARP table
route -n                # Routing table
```

